📊 FMCG Sales, Marketing & Profitability Dashboard (2023–2025)
🔷 Project Overview

This project presents a comprehensive Tableau dashboard analyzing FMCG (Fast-Moving Consumer Goods) data from 2023 to 2025. The goal is to uncover actionable insights into sales performance, profitability, marketing efficiency, and operational costs.

The dashboard is designed to support data-driven decision-making for business stakeholders by transforming raw data into interactive visual insights.

🎯 Objectives
Analyze overall sales and revenue trends
Evaluate profitability across regions, brands, and categories
Measure marketing effectiveness (ROI)
Identify cost drivers and inefficiencies
Highlight top-performing products and channels
📁 Dataset Description

The dataset contains FMCG business metrics including:
Sales (Gross & Net Revenue)
Profit and Profit Margin
Units Sold
Marketing Spend
Discounts
Cost of Goods Sold (COGS)
Logistics Cost
Product, Brand, and Category details
Sales Channels and Promotion Types
Time-based data (Date, Year, Month)

📊 Dashboard Features
🔹 Executive Overview
Total Sales
Net Revenue
Total Profit
Profit Margin
Units Sold

🔹 Sales Analysis
Sales trend over time (Monthly/Yearly)
Regional sales comparison
Category-wise performance

🔹 Profitability Insights
Profit by brand and category
Profit margin distribution
High vs low performing products

🔹 Marketing Performance
Marketing Spend vs Revenue
ROI by Promotion Type
Impact of discounts on sales

🔹 Operational Analysis
Logistics cost by region
Cost vs profit comparison
Channel performance insights

⚙️ Tools & Technologies
Tableau – Data visualization & dashboard development
Excel/CSV – Data source
DAX (optional) – Used for advanced calculations (if replicated in Power BI)

📈 Key Insights
Certain regions consistently outperform others in both sales and profit.
High marketing spend does not always guarantee higher ROI.
Some product categories generate strong revenue but lower profit margins.
Logistics and operational costs significantly impact profitability.

🚀 How to Use
Download the .twbx Tableau file from this repository
Open using Tableau Desktop / Tableau Public
Interact with filters and visuals to explore insights

💡 Future Improvements
Add predictive analytics (sales forecasting)
Integrate real-time data sources
Enhance dashboard storytelling with advanced KPIs

